[b]Trading Range State Machine[/b] identifies active trading ranges and tracks their maturity through a state machine — from first formation to confirmed breakout.

[b]What it does[/b]

Range boundaries are built from clustering recent pivot highs and lows (falling back to a simple highest/lowest window when no reliable cluster forms). An 8-factor weighted score then measures how strongly current price action actually behaves like a range, driving the range through five states: Inactive, Building, Confirmed, Mature, and Breaking.

[b]Score components[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Efficiency Ratio[/b] — low net-to-total movement favors a range
[*][b]Candle Overlap[/b] — high bar-to-bar overlap favors a range
[*][b]Choppiness[/b] — high choppiness favors a range
[*][b]Structure Chaos[/b] — few structure breaks favor a range
[*][b]Regression Flatness[/b] — flat slope, weak trend correlation favors a range
[*][b]Boundary Stability[/b] — balanced, repeated touches of the same levels favor a range
[*][b]ATR Compression[/b] — volatility below its longer-term average favors a range
[*][b]Mean Reversion[/b] — repeated returns to the range midpoint favor a range
[/list]

[b]Visuals[/b]

[list]
[*]Range lines and midline, drawn only while a range is active
[*]Touch markers at the upper/lower boundaries
[*]Background heat that scales continuously with range score within each state
[*]Bottom ribbon colored by state, with breakouts colored bullish (green) or bearish (red) by direction
[*]Dashboard with state, score, position-in-range (% + zone), breakout direction, and component breakdown
[/list]

